'''Jurriën David Norman Timber''' ({{IPA|nl|ˈjʏri(j)ɛn ˈtɪmbər}};<ref>{{Cite web |date=23 July 2022 |title=Q&A TIMBER & WIJNDAL 💬 – 'Owen, do you wanna go on a date with me?' 😳 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=OmnFHaLiUcs&t=2s |access-date=30 July 2023 |via=YouTube |publisher=[[AFC Ajax]] |language=Dutch}}</ref> born 17 June 2001) is a Dutch professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defender (association football)|defender]] for {{English football updater|Arsenal}} club [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands national team]]. Considered one of the best right-backs in the world, he is known for his athleticism, versatility, composure, and ball control.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-06-04 |title=2025 FC 100: Alexander-Arnold among best fullbacks in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45164388/2025-fc-100-alexander-arnold-best-fullbacks-mens-soccer |access-date=2025-11-24 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=30 June 2025 |title=The 25 Best Right Backs in World Soccer—Ranked |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/the-best-right-backs-in-world-soccer-ranked |access-date=9 January 2026 |website=SI |language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=12 December 2025 |title=Ranked! The 20 best right-backs in the world |url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/person/player/best-right-backs-in-the-world |access-date=9 January 2026 |website=FourFourTwo |language=en}}</ref>

Timber joined [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]]'s youth academy in 2014, from [[Feyenoord]], together with his twin brother [[Quinten Timber|Quinten]]. He made his first-team debut for Ajax in March 2020, and won two [[Eredivisie]] titles and one [[KNVB Cup]]. He signed for Arsenal in July 2023, for an initial transfer fee of £34 million from Eredivisie club Ajax.

Timber made 29 appearances for the Netherlands at youth international level. He was a member of the [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|under-17]] team that won the [[2018 UEFA European Under-17 Championship]]. He made his senior international debut in June 2021.

==Club career==
===Youth career===
Timber started playing for [[Utrecht]]-based club DVSU at the age of four, before joining [[Feyenoord]]'s youth system when he was six.<ref name="earlycareer">{{cite news |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2294521-jurrien-en-quinten-timber-de-nieuwe-frank-en-ronald-bij-ajax |title=Jurriën en Quinten Timber, de nieuwe Frank en Ronald bij Ajax |trans-title=Jurriën and Quinten Timber, the new Frank and Ronald at Ajax |website=nos.nl |language=nl |date=22 July 2019 |access-date=20 November 2022}}</ref> In 2014, he joined [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], where he signed his first professional contract in 2018.<ref name="earlycareer"/>

===Ajax===
Timber made his senior debut for Ajax in a 3–1 win over [[SC Heerenveen]] on 7 March 2020.{{citation needed|date=March 2024}}

He scored his first career goal for Ajax against [[FC Emmen|Emmen]] on 2 May 2021.<ref name=ERE /> It was the opening goal in an eventual 4–0 win. That result confirmed Ajax as [[2020–21 Eredivisie|Eredivisie]] champions for a record 35th time.<ref name=ERE />

=== Arsenal ===

On 14 July 2023, it was announced that Timber had joined [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] from [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]] on a long-term contract and would wear the number 12, previously worn by [[William Saliba]].<ref>{{cite web |date=14 July 2023 |title=Jurrien Timber signs for Arsenal |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/jurrien-timber-signs-arsenal |accessdate=14 July 2023 |website=Arsenal FC}}</ref> Arsenal paid Ajax an initial transfer fee of £34&nbsp;million, with the deal containing add-ons that could raise the fee to £38.5&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jurrien Timber: Arsenal sign Ajax & Netherlands defender for £34m |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66017042 |website=BBC Sport |date=14 July 2023 |access-date=15 July 2023}}</ref> On 6 August, he made his competitive debut for the club against [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] in the [[2023 FA Community Shield|Community Shield]], which Arsenal won 4–1 on penalties.<ref>{{Cite web |date=6 August 2023 |title=Arsenal 1–1 Man City (4–1 on pens) |work=Sky Sports |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/arsenal-vs-manchester-city/report/482389 |language=en}}</ref> Timber made his [[Premier League]] debut in a 2–1 home win over [[Nottingham Forest]] on 12 August. He limped off in the 50th minute with an injury. It was later confirmed that he had suffered an [[Anterior cruciate ligament|ACL]] injury on his right knee which would require surgery and keep him out of the game for a "period of time".<ref>{{cite web | title=Timber suffers ACL injury and faces surgery | website=BBC Sport | date=16 August 2023 | url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66524799 | access-date=16 August 2023}}</ref> In February 2024, he was included in the club's squad for the [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Champions League knockout phase]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=When will Jurrien Timber be back? Arsenal drop hint on Dutchman's ACL injury recovery as updated Champions League squad is revealed |work=Goal (website) |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/jurrien-timber-back-arsenal-drop-major-hint-dutchman-almost-recovered-acl-injury/bltce326258416ee62a#csc8f6084e729f7327 |date=6 February 2024}}</ref>

On 22 April 2024, Timber made his comeback in [[Arsenal F.C. Under-21s and Academy|Arsenal Under-21s]]' [[Professional Development League|Premier League 2]] game against [[Blackburn Rovers F.C. Under-23s and Academy|Blackburn Rovers]], playing the first half and scoring the opening goal in a 2–2 draw at [[Ewood Park]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/under-21/2024-Apr-22/blackburn-rovers-u21-2-2-under-21-match-report|title=U21s Report: Blackburn Rovers 2–2 Arsenal|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|first=Brian|last=Matovu|date=22 April 2024|access-date=23 April 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.premierleague.com/match/107647/premier-league-2/2023-24/blackburn-rovers-u21-v-arsenal-u21|title=Premier League 2: Blackburn Rovers U21 v Arsenal U21, 2023/24|publisher=Premier League|date=22 April 2024|access-date=23 April 2024}}</ref> He made his first-team comeback on 19 May, coming on as a 69th-minute substitute for [[Ben White (footballer)|Ben White]] in Arsenal's final-day win against [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]. Timber said he "felt so good after so many months of hard work" and "it's just nice for me to go into the summer with some minutes."<ref>{{cite news|title=Timber reflects on an emotional first-team return|first=Jonathon|last=Rogers|date=20 May 2024|access-date=21 May 2024|publisher=Arsenal F.C.|url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/timber-reflects-emotional-first-team-return}}</ref>

====2024–Present: Return and starting role====
On 4 December 2024, Timber scored his first goal for Arsenal from a header in a 2–0 victory against [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] at the [[Emirates Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2024-Dec-04/arsenal-2-0-manchester-united-match-report |title=Report: Arsenal 2–0 Manchester United |publisher=Arsenal F.C. |date=4 December 2024 }}</ref> On 4 March 2025, he netted his first Champions League goal in a 7–1 away win over [[PSV Eindhoven]] during the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Round of 16]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Howell |first=Alex |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c8j00ke2r23t |title=PSV 1–7 Arsenal |work=BBC Sport |date=4 March 2025 }}</ref> Timber received widespread praise for his defensive performance in Arsenal’s Champions League quarter-final win over [[Real Madrid]], with fans highlighting his ability to neutralize [[Vinícius Júnior]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://tbrfootball.com/arsenal-fans-are-all-saying-the-same-thing-about-jurrien-timber-after-2-1-win-vs-real-madrid/ |title=Arsenal fans are all saying the same thing about Jurrien Timber after 2–1 win vs Real Madrid |website=TBR Football |date=16 April 2025 |access-date=19 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.givemesport.com/arsenal-fans-praise-unbelievable-performance-monster-real-madrid-jurrien-timber/ |title=Arsenal fans praise 'unbelievable' performance of Timber against Real Madrid |website=GiveMeSport |date=16 April 2025 |access-date=19 September 2025}}</ref>

Having played 48 matches across all competitions, including 30 in the Premier League and 13 in the Champions League, Jurrien Timber cemented his place as Arsenal’s starting right-back.<ref>{{cite web |last=Campbell |first=Jordan |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5805427/2024/10/01/jurrien-timber-arsenal-back/ |title=How Jurrien Timber fought his way back – and why his return has changed Arsenal |website=The Athletic via The New York Times |date=1 October 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last= |first= |url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/arsenal-ben-white-must-respond-060010236.html |title=Ben White must respond as Jurrien Timber shows Mikel Arteta what he's missing |website=Yahoo Sports |date=11 April 2025 |access-date=19 September 2025}}</ref>

On 23 August 2025, Timber won [[Player of the match#Association football|Man of the match]] against [[Leeds United]], as he netted twice and assisted once in the 5–0 home thrashing.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Arsenal 5–0 Leeds United Match Report |url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-Aug-23/arsenal-5-0-leeds-united-match-report |website=Arsenal.com |date=23 August 2025 |access-date=25 September 2025}}</ref>

An outstanding October for Timber saw him nominated for the [[2025–26 Premier League#Monthly awards|Premier League Player of the Month]] award for the first time.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Help Timber win Premier League Player of the Month |url=https://www.arsenal.com/news/help-timber-win-premier-league-player-month|website=Arsenal.com|date=30 October 2025 |access-date=29 November 2025|language=en|first=Jonathon|last=Rogers}}</ref> During the month, Timber was part of an Arsenal backline that kept three clean sheets in three consecutive league wins over fellow London sides [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham]], [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]], and [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=October 2025 EA SPORTS Player of the Month nominees |url=https://www.premierleague.com/en/news/4449748|website=Premier League|date=30 October 2025 |access-date=29 November 2025|language=en}}</ref>

On 26 November, in a [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]] fixture against leaders [[Bayern Munich]], Timber scored the opening goal, heading in a corner from close range. Arsenal would win the match 3–1.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Report: Arsenal 3–1 Bayern MunichHotspur|url=https://www.arsenal.com/fixture/arsenal/2025-Nov-26/arsenal-3-1-bayern-munich-match-report|access-date=29 November 2025|last=James|first=Josh|website=Arsenal.com|language=en}}</ref>

==International career==
Timber played youth international football for the Netherlands at under-15,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185192/uitslagen |title=Jeugd mannen onder 15 uitslagen |trans-title=Youth men under 15 results |website=onsoranje.nl |language=nl |access-date=20 November 2022}}</ref> [[Netherlands national under-16 football team|under-16]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185191/speler/18786 |title=Jurrien Maduro Jeugd mannen onder 16 |trans-title=Jurrien Maduro Youth men under 16 |website=onsoranje.nl |language=nl |access-date=20 November 2022}}</ref> [[Netherlands national under-17 football team|under-17]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/184965/speler/18786 |title=Jurrien Timber Jeugd mannen onder 17 |trans-title=Jurrien Timber Youth men under 17 |website=onsoranje.nl |language=nl |access-date=20 November 2022}}</ref> [[Netherlands national under-19 football team|under-19]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185189/speler/18786 |title=Jurrien Timber Jeugd mannen onder 19 |trans-title=Jurrien Timber Youth men under 19 |website=onsoranje.nl |language=nl |access-date=20 November 2022}}</ref> and [[Netherlands national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.onsoranje.nl/teams/185185/speler/18786 |title=Jurrien Timber Jong Oranje |trans-title=Jurrien Timber Young Orange |website=onsoranje.nl |language=nl |access-date=20 November 2022}}</ref> He was selected for the senior [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]] squad for [[UEFA Euro 2020]]. He made his debut for the team on 2 June 2021, as a starter in a friendly against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=[[ESPN]]|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/lineups?gameId=600284|title=Netherlands v Scotland game report|date=2 June 2021}}</ref>

Timber was included in the final selection of the Netherlands team for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] by manager [[Louis van Gaal]] in November 2022.<ref>{{cite tweet|number=1583413124987658240|user=OnsOranje|title=🦁 𝐏𝐫𝐨𝐯𝐢𝐬𝐢𝐨𝐧𝐚𝐥 𝐒𝐪𝐮𝐚𝐝: This is the longlist of 39 players where our final World Cup 2022 squad will be selected from! 📋 |date=21 October 2022}}</ref> After missing the opening [[2022 FIFA World Cup Group A|group stage]] win against [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]],<ref>{{Cite news |title=Late goals give Dutch victory over Senegal |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63619381 |access-date=29 November 2022}}</ref> he played 90 minutes in the 1–1 draw against [[Ecuador national football team|Ecuador]]<ref>{{Cite news |title=Valencia scores as Ecuador draw with Netherlands |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63672202 |access-date=29 November 2022}}</ref> and the 2–0 win against [[Qatar national football team|Qatar]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Gakpo nets again as Dutch beat Qatar to top group |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63711993 |access-date=29 November 2022}}</ref> He again played 90 minutes in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]] win against the [[United States men's national soccer team|United States]]<ref>{{Cite news |title=Dutch overcome USA to book quarter-final spot |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63765128 |access-date=3 December 2022}}</ref> as well as the entirety of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Quarter-finals|quarter-final]] match against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]], which the Netherlands eventually lost on [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|penalties]] and so were subsequently eliminated from the tournament.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Argentina beat the Netherlands in penalty shootout to reach semi-finals |website=BBC Sport |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63830319 |access-date=9 December 2022}}</ref>

After missing [[UEFA Euro 2024]] due to injury, Timber was recalled to the Netherlands' squad for their opening matches of the [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League]] in September 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/timber-back-dutch-squad-twin-brother-also-called-up-2024-08-30/|title=Timber back in Dutch squad and twin brother also called up|date=30 August 2024|website=Reuters}}</ref> In the match against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia & Herzegovina]] on 8 September, he appeared as a substitute in the 83rd minute, lining up alongside his brother Quinten for the first time in senior football. This made the Timber brothers the third pair of twins to represent the Netherlands together after [[René van de Kerkhof|René]] and [[Willy van de Kerkhof]] and [[Frank de Boer|Frank]] and [[Ronald de Boer]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jeugdjournaal.nl/artikel/2536413-tweeling-timber-speelt-in-oranje-gebeurt-bijna-nooit|title=Tweeling Timber speelt in Oranje: 'Gebeurt bijna nooit'|language=Dutch|date=8 September 2024|website=NOS jeugdjournaal}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Born in the Netherlands, Timber and his twin brother, [[Quinten Timber|Quinten]], who is also a footballer, are of [[Curaçaoans in the Netherlands|Curaçaoan descent]]. Both their mother, Marilyn, and their father hail from [[Curaçao]], part of the [[ABC islands (Leeward Antilles)|ABC Islands]] in the [[Dutch Caribbean]]. Due to past situations, the family took on their maternal name Timber instead of taking the last name of their father Maduro.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ajaxshowtime.com/article/hoofdnieuws/120799/het-verhaal-achter-de-gebroeders-timber|title=Het Verhaal Achter: De gebroeders Timber|website=Ajax Showtime|date=8 March 2020 }}</ref> The twins also have three older brothers Shamier, Chris, and [[Dylan Timber|Dylan]], the latter of whom is also a footballer who represents [[Curaçao national football team|Curaçao]] on an international level.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ajax.nl/streams/jeugd/we-zijn-gewoon-de-nieuwe-timbers.htm|title='We zijn gewoon de nieuwe Timbers'|website=Ajax}}</ref>

Timber is a Christian, and often shares Bible verses through his social media accounts before games.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://twitter.com/JurrienTimber |title= Jurrien Timber twitter profile}}</ref>{{Primary source inline|date=June 2025}}

Timber is in a relationship with Rose de Back.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-07-09 |title=Arsenal's Bukayo Saka meets Carlos Alcaraz after taking girlfriend Tolami Benson to watch Spanish tennis star's Wimbledon quarter-final win over Cameron Norrie {{!}} Goal.com Australia |url=https://www.goal.com/en-au/lists/arsenal-bukayo-saka-carlos-alcaraz-girlfriend-tolami-benson-spanish-tennis-star-wimbledon-quarter-final-win-cameron-norrie/blt25ab40219f58c72e |access-date=2025-07-11 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-AU}}</ref>

